╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 1.2: Word Motion                      ║
║  Category: Movement              Difficulty: ★☆☆ Fundamental    ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  w     Move to next word start (selects the word)
  b     Move to previous word start
  e     Move to next word end
  W     Move to next WORD start (ignores punctuation)
  B     Move to previous WORD start
  E     Move to next WORD end

MNEMONIC: w=word, b=back, e=end. Uppercase = WORD (whitespace-delimited)

NOTE: In Helix, w selects from cursor to the start of the next word.
      This means pressing w then d deletes a word — select, then act!

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  Delete every other word to transform each sentence.
  Use  w  to select a word, then  d  to delete it.

  Tip: After deleting, you may need to also delete the extra space.
  Try  w d  for each word you want to remove.

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

one two three four five six seven eight
alpha bravo charlie delta echo foxtrot
red orange yellow green blue indigo violet

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

one three five seven
alpha charlie echo
red yellow blue violet

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: Position at start of "two", press w to select it,
          then d to delete. You'll also need to handle the space.
  Hint 2: Try selecting the word AND the following space before
          deleting: w on the word, then l to extend into the space,
          then d.
  Hint 3: Alternative approach — use v to enter select mode, then
          w to extend across the word + space, then d.
